gurmukhi: ਸਭ ਜਗ ਕੋ ਜੁ ਧਨੰਤਰਿ ਦੀਅਾ || ਕਲਪ ਬ੍ਰਿਛ ਲਛਮੀ ਕਰ ਲੀਅਾ ||
transliteration: Sabh Jag Ko Ju Dhanantar(i) Deeaa|| Kalap Brichh Lachhmikar Leeaa||
translation: Dhanwantri was given for the world and the wish-fulfilling tree and Lakshmi were given to gods.

gurmukhi: ਸਿਵ ਮਾਹੁਰ ਰੰਭਾ ਸਭ ਲੋਕਨ || ਸੁਖ ਕਰਤਾ ਹਰਤਾ ਸਭ ਸੋਕਨ ||੫||
transliteration: Siv Maahur Ranbhaa Sabh Lokan|| Soukh Kartaa Hartaa Sabh Sokan||5||
translation: Shiva was given the poison and Rambha, the heavenly damsel, was given to al other people; she was the giver of al comforts and the destroyer of the sufferings.5.

gurmukhi: ਸਸਿ ਕ੍ਰਿਸ ਦੇ ਕਰਬੇ ਨਮਿਤ ਮਨਿ ਲਛਮੀ ਕਰ ਲੀਨ ||
transliteration: Sas(i) Kris De Karbe Namit Man(i) Lachhmikar Leen||
translation: Maha Mohini took the moon in his own hand for giving it to someone and also the gem and Laksmi for keeping it with herself;

gurmukhi: ੳੁਰ ਰਾਖੀ ਤਿਹ ਤੇ ਚਮਕ ਪ੍ਰਗਟ ਦਿਖਾੲੀ ਦੀਨ ||੬||
transliteration: Ur Raakhitih Te Chamak Pragt Dikhaaideen||6||
translation: She concealed the gem and Lakshmi for keeping it with herself;

gurmukhi: ਗਾੲਿ ਰਖੀਸਨ ਕੳੁ ਦੲੀ ਕਹ ਲੳੁ ਕਰੋਂ ਬਿਚਾਰ ||
transliteration: Gaae Rakheesan Kau Daikah Lau Karon Bichar ||
translation: The wish-fulfilling cow was given to the sages; how far can I describe all these things;

gurmukhi: ਸਾਸਤ੍ਰ ਸੋਧ ਕਬੀਅਨ ਮੁਖਨ ਲੀਜਹੁ ਪੂਛ ਸੁਧਾਰ ||੭||
transliteration: Sasstra Soddh Kabiann  Moukhan Leejay Poucch Sudhaar||7||
translation: You may improve (their description) by feflecting on the Shastras and asking the poets.7.

gurmukhi: ਰਹੇ ਰੀਝ ਅੈਸੇ ਸਭੈ ਦੇਵ ਦਾਨੰ || ਮ੍ਰਿਗੀ ਰਾਜ ਜੈਸੇ ਸੁਨੇ ਨਾਦ ਕਾਨੰ ||
transliteration: Rahe Reejh Aise Sabhai Dev Daanan|| Mrigiraaj Jaise Soune Naad Kaanan||
translation: Both the gods and demons were swinging like the king or deer, who gets absorbed in the sound of music.

gurmukhi: ਬਟੇ ਰਤਨ ਸਰਬੰ ਗੲੀ ਛੂਟ ਰਾਰੰ || ਧਰਯੋ ਅੈਸ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਬਿਸਨ ਪੰਚਮ ਵਤਾਰੰ ||੮||
transliteration: Bade Ratan Saraban Gadchhodht Raaran|| Ddaryo Ais Sribisan Pancham Vataaran||
translation: All the jewels were distributed and the dispute ended; in this way, the fifth incarnation of the Vishnu became apparent.8.

gurmukhi: ੲਿਤਿ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਬਚਿਤ੍ਰ ਨਾਟਕੇ ਗ੍ਰੰਥੇ ਮਹਾ ਮੋਹਨੀ ਪੰਚਮ ਅਵਤਾਰ ਸੰਪੂਰਨ ||੫||
transliteration: It(i) Sribachitra Naatake Granthe Mahaa Mohani Pancham Avtaar Sanpooran||5||
translation: End of the description of the fifth incarnation MAHA MOHNI in BACHITTAR NATAK.5.
